radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal atelectasis or scarring at the left lung base, without evidence of focal pneumonia.
Sinus rhythm at a rate of 60 beats per minute, with premature atrial complexes and nonspecific ST-segment and T-wave changes.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Right coronary artery with mild diffuse disease; 30% ostial stenosis in the posterior descending artery; 90% focal proximal stenosis in the posterolateral ventricular branch.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Successful placement of a bare-metal stent in the posterolateral ventricular branch, with excellent angiographic results and no residual stenosis.
